
[1]pennyworth

   PEN'NYWORTH, n. As much as is bought for a penny.

   1. Any purchase; any thing bought or sold for money; that which is
   worth the money given.

   2. A good bargain; something advantageously purchased, or for less than
   it is worth.

   3. A small quantity.
